create documents, install apps, and do other work, you can create new folders to keep yourself organized.</p><div id=\"mchlp8436efe\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-mchlp8436efe\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Create a folder</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchlp8436efe\"><ol><li><p>On your Mac, click the Finder icon <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/937fa92677a2c49a18fa81070e5d8419.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconDefault_Finder.png\"> in the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=dock&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL8AC6483E&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Dock</a> to open a Finder window, then navigate to where you want to create the folder.</p><p>Alternatively, click the desktop if you want to create the folder on the desktop.</p></li><li><p>Choose File &gt; New Folder, or press Shift-Command-N.</p><p>If the New Folder command is dimmed, you can’t create a folder in the current location.</p></li><li><p>Enter a name for the folder, then press Return.</p></li></ol></div></div><div id=\"mchlp8cd8f79\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-mchlp8cd8f79\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Move items into folders</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchlp8cd8f79\"><ol><li><p>On your Mac, click the Finder icon <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/937fa92677a2c49a18fa81070e5d8419.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconDefault_Finder.png\"> in the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=dock&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL8AC6483E&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Dock</a> to open a Finder window.</p></li><li><p>Do any of the following:</p><ul><li><p><em>Put an item in a folder: </em><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=drag-and-drop&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL297B12B0&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Drag it</a> to the folder.</p></li><li><p><em>Put several items in a folder: </em><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=select-items&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLB6D352A4&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Select the items</a>, then drag one of the items to the folder.</p><p>All selected items move to the folder.</p></li><li><p><em>Keep an item in its original location and put a copy in a folder: </em>Press and hold the Option key, then drag the item to the folder.</p></li><li><p><em>Keep an item in its original location and put an alias for it in a new folder: </em>Press and hold the Option and Command keys, then drag the item to the folder to create the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=alias&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL108233D3&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">alias</a>.</p></li><li><p><em>Make a copy of an item within the same folder: </em>Select the item, then choose File &gt; Duplicate or press Command-D.</p></li><li><p><em>Copy files to a different disk: </em>Drag the files to the disk.</p></li><li><p><em>Move files to a different disk: </em>Press and hold the Command key, then drag the files to the disk.</p></li></ul></li></ol></div></div><div id=\"mchlp12c44ac\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-mchlp12c44ac\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Quickly group multiple items into a folder</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchlp12c44ac\"><p>You can quickly create a folder of items on the desktop or in a <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=finder&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLAAB6CFC4&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Finder</a> window.</p><ol><li><p>On your Mac, <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=select-items&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLB6D352A4&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">select all the items</a> you want to group together.</p></li><li><p>Control-click one of the selected items, then choose New Folder with Selection.</p></li><li><p>Enter a name for the folder, then press Return.</p></li></ol></div></div><div id=\"mchlp02d9935\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-mchlp02d9935\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Merge two folders with the same name</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchlp02d9935\"><p>If you have two folders with identical names at two different locations, you can merge them into a single folder. </p><ul class=\"ListSingle\"><li><p>On your Mac, press and hold the Option key, then <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=drag-and-drop&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL297B12B0&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">drag one folder</a> to the location that contains a folder with the same name. In the dialog that appears, click Merge.</p><p>The Merge option appears only if one of the folders contains items that are not in the other folder. If the folders contain different versions of identically named files, the only options are Stop or Replace.</p></li></ul></div></div><p>To organize your files automatically, <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=create-or-change-a-smart-folder-on-mac&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP2804&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">use Smart Folders</a>. Smart Folders automatically gather files by type and subject matter, and are instantly updated as you change, add, and remove files on your Mac.</p><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=store-files-in-icloud-drive&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLE5A61431&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use iCloud Drive to store documents on your Mac and iOS devices</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=get-file-folder-and-disk-information-on-mac&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP1774&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Get file, folder, and disk information on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=rename-files-folders-and-disks-on-mac&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP1144&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Rename files, folders, and disks on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=delete-files-and-folders-on-mac&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP1093&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Delete files and folders on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=finder&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP2605&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">See and organize your files in the Finder on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=manage-icloud-storage&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH36833&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Manage iCloud storage on Mac</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["DisplayVersion/macOS Mojave 10.14","IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","ContentMode/liveContent","ArchivalStatus/Unarchived","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexON","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"3950"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"7864"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"Unarchived","name":"Unarchived","englishName":"Unarchived","displayName":"Unarchived","articleCount":"10186"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndexON","name":"ExternalIndexON","englishName":"ExternalIndexON","displayName":"ExternalIndexON","articleCount":"4683"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"7818"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac",